Class EasyMockTestCase

java.lang.Object
  junit.framework.Assert
      junit.framework.TestCase
          org.easymock.jdk14.EasyMockTestCase
All Implemented Interfaces:
junit.framework.Test
public abstract class EasyMockTestCase
extends junit.framework.TestCase

A junit test case that provides all the easy mock methods. This class compensates for the lack of static imports in JDK 1.4.

A test case can extend this class and use the Easymock methods without any imports. The methods in this class are delegates to the actual EasyMock class.

Author:
Srikanth
See Also:
EasyMock

getCurrentArguments

public java.lang.Object[] getCurrentArguments()
Returns the arguments of the currenObject mock method call, if inside an IAnswer callback - be careful here, reordering parameters of method changes the semantics of your tests.

Returns:
the arguments of the currenObject mock method call.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if called outside of IAnswer callbacks.
